Find the dominant eigenvalue and its corresponding eigenvector for the following 3x3 matrix using the power iteration method: 

A = [1, 2, 3; 
     2, 3, 4; 
     3, 4, 5] 

Starting with the initial guess vector x0 = [1;1;1], perform 5 iterations of the power iteration method and provide the resulting approximation of the dominant eigenvalue and its corresponding eigenvector.
